<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 9:17PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Hutchinson, eastern
Hansford, western Roberts and western Ochiltree Counties through 945
PM CDT...
At 917 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 8 miles northeast of Gruver to 12 miles south
of Spearman to Borger. Movement was east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Borger, Spearman, Stinnett, Gruver, Farnsworth, Waka, Pringle and
Morse.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
